# .htpasswd.example — sample format for the Basic-Auth password file
#
# NEVER commit the real .htpasswd — it is gitignored.
# The real file MUST live ABOVE public_html on the server (e.g. /home/USER/.htpasswd).
# Its path must match the AuthUserFile directive in .htaccess.
#
# Generate the real file on the server (or locally and upload above public_html):
#
#   htpasswd -c /home/USER/.htpasswd preview
#
# The -c flag creates the file. Omit it if you are adding a second user to an
# existing file. Replace "preview" with your chosen username.
#
# Sample line (DO NOT use this hash — generate a fresh one):
preview:$apr1$example1$REPLACETHISWITHAREALHASH00000/
